fork /fɔːk/

(forking,forked,forks) 

1. N-COUNT A fork is a tool used for eating food which has a row of three or four long metal points at the end. 餐叉 

例： ...knives and forks. ...刀和叉。 

2. N-COUNT A fork in a road, path, or river is a point at which it divides into two parts and forms a 'Y' shape. (道路、河流等的) 岔口 

例： We arrived at a fork in the road. 我们来到了该路的一个岔口。 

例： The road divides; you should take the right fork. 路分岔了；你应该走右岔路。 

3. V-T If you fork food into your mouth or onto a plate, you put it there using a fork. 叉起 

例： He forked an egg onto a piece of bread and folded it into a sandwich. 他叉起一个鸡蛋放到一片面包上并将其折成了一个三明治。 

4. V-I If a road, path, or river forks , it forms a fork. (公路、路径、河流等) 分岔 [no cont] 

例： Beyond the village the road forked. 过了那个村子公路就分岔了。 

5. N-COUNT A garden fork is a tool used for breaking up soil which has a row of three or four long metal points at the end. 耙 [英国英语]

